  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      A buccal swab will be taken using a cotton stick by rubbing it against the buccal mucosa.
      Samples will be taken from the same participant at different timepoints.

      DNA will be extracted from the buccal cells on the swabs using a commercial extraction kit
      and will be quantified by a nano-drop spectrophotometer.

      We will determine global and gene-specific methylation and hydroxymethylation alterations by
      UPLC/MS/MS. Hydrolyzed DNA into individual nucleosides will be analyzed for the quantitative
      measurement of 5-methylCytosine and 5-hydroxymethylCytosine on Triple Quadrupole UPLC/MS/MS
      platform. Secondly, specific methylation in the CpG islands of tumor suppressor and promoter
      genes, and genes involved in the oxidative stress pathways will be assessed by
      PCR-pyrosequencing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
